        "header": "1Introduction",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.11707/2604.11707v1/x1.png",
                "caption": "Figure 1:Overview of the proposedRe2Pixhierarchical framework during inference.In Stage 1, semantic featuresh1:Mh_{1:M}of the context frames are extracted from a vision foundation model (VFM) encoderEhE_{h}and fed into a masked feature transformer to autoregressively predict (in frame-wise way) future semantic VFM featuresh^M+1:K\\hat{h}_{M+1:K}.\nIn Stage 2, both the pasth^1:M\\hat{h}_{1:M}and predicted featuresh^M+1:K\\hat{h}_{M+1:K}condition the diffusion transformerGzG_{z}to generate future VAE latentsz^M+1:K\\hat{z}_{M+1:K},\nwhich are then decoded into RGB future frames.",
                "position": 291
            }
        ]
    },
